Career High Assists: 3, three times

CAREER NOTES

79 games played ... 402 points, 198 rebounds and 40 assists ... 53% from the field

AS A SENIOR (2022-2023)

One of the Lopers top reserves again ... played in all 28 games with six starts (final six games) ... came in at 7.3 points and 3.5 rebounds per game ... 10 double figure games ... shot 52% from the field ... 20 points on 8 of 9 shooting vs. Missouri Western ... had 11 and 14 points, respectively, in the next two games ... shot 68% from the field over these three games ... 14 points at Central Missouri ... in season-finale vs. Fort Hays, a career-best 13 boards (10 defensive)

AS A JUNIOR (2021-2022)

One of the Lopers top reserves ... played in 25 games with a start ... finished up at 5.9 points and 2.4 rebounds per game ... shot 54% from the field ... five double digit games ... career-best 22 points came in home win over Sterling (Kan.) College ... made 11 of 17 shots over 24 minutes ... also grabbed three o-boards ... three games earlier, went for 21 points in road loss to Emporia State ... went 10 of 13 from the field in 26 minutes of work ... also had seven rebounds (three offensive) ... later in the year, 11 points (4 of 5 FG shooting) vs. national power NW Missouri

AS A SOPHOMORE (2020-2021)

Reserve forward ... played in 17 games averaging 14 minutes an appearance ... shot 54% from the field ... 3.4 points and 2.9 rebounds per game ... nine points and four rebounds in season-high 23 minutes vs. NCAA Tourney qualifier Washburn ... eight points and four boards the next game at Central Oklahoma ... later in the year had eight points and four rebounds in home win vs. Central Missouri

AS A FRESHMAN (2019-2020)

Appeared in 13 games, all off the bench ... missed some time due to injury ... 10 of 20 from the field ... finished with 27 points, 16 boards, six assists and two blocks ... 10 points, five rebounds and an assist in season-opening loss at Oklahoma Baptist ... five points and three rebounds in nine minutes of work in a road loss to Fort Hays State

HIGH SCHOOL

Helped the Warriors (27-2) win the 2018 Class C-1 state title after finishing runner up a year earlier ... in the 2018 state title game win over Winnebago, came off the bench to provide a game-high 19 points, six rebounds and three assists ... honorable mention all-state ... finished season at 10.0 points, 4.7 rebounds, 1.5 assists and 1.0 steals per game ... numbers jumped to 20 points and seven rebounds per game as a senior ... subsequently first-team Class C1 all-state ... shot well over 50% from the field his final three years ... member of the Bison Nebraska 17U boys select team in the summer of 2018 ... in the summer of 2019 played in the NCA All-Star game ... scored a team-best 24 points to help Blue team win in OT
